In this article, President Barack Obama sends a letter to the Speaker of the House of Representatives regarding fiscal year 2013 budget amendments. The amendments include changes for various departments, such as Defense, Health and Human Services, Homeland Security, Housing and Urban Development, State, and the Corps of Engineers. There is also an amendment to a general provision that applies to the entire government. These amendments will not increase the overall discretionary budget authority. Additionally, the President includes amendments for the Legislative Branch, which are transmitted without change as a matter of comity and tradition. The purpose of these amendments is to accurately reflect the policies assumed in the FY 2013 Budget.